## Architecture

**The boundary that must not cross:**
- `src/{{repo_name}}/models/` — pure networks: take tensors in, return tensors out. No loss, no optimizer, no Lightning.
- `src/{{repo_name}}/barebones_lightningmodule.py` — owns everything else: `training_step`, `validation_step`, loss, optimizer, scheduler.

**Hydra config composition:**
`configs/train_config.yaml` is the single entry point. It composes sub-configs from `configs/model/`, `configs/data/`, `configs/trainer/`, etc. Override any value on the CLI: `python src/{{repo_name}}/train.py trainer.max_epochs=50`.

**Where to start:**
1. Implement your network in `src/{{repo_name}}/models/` (return raw tensor, no loss)
2. Wire loss + optimizer in `barebones_lightningmodule.py`
3. Implement `BarebonesDataModule` in `src/{{repo_name}}/data/barebones_datamodule.py`
4. Add/edit Hydra config groups under `configs/`

## Key files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `src/{{repo_name}}/barebones_lightningmodule.py` | Training logic — implement this |
| `src/{{repo_name}}/data/barebones_datamodule.py` | Data loading — implement this |
| `configs/train_config.yaml` | Root Hydra config; controls everything |
| `configs/model/default_model.yaml` | Model hyperparameters |
